[thinking] **Considering resource handling**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about whether to use ClassLoader.getSystemResource(MARKER) directly. I wonder if we should include a fallback for when the marker is null to avoid failing natively. If the marker is null, it would throw a NullPointerException, which could cause a test to fail. It might be a good idea to catch that NPE and assert instead, so I’ll explore this option a bit more.
[thinking] 
